article.description: Lotanna Nwogbo had 19 points on 8-of-10 shooting and Longwood led by double digits throughout the second half to beat Campbell 74-57 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Longwood maintains in 2nd half to beat Campbell 74-57
article.linkText: Longwood maintains in 2nd half to beat Campbell 74-57
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. -- Lotanna Nwogbo had 19 points on 8-of-10 shooting and Longwood led by double digits throughout the second half to beat Campbell 74-57 on Thursday night. Tra'Vaughn White scored 18 and Shaquille Johnson had 12 points and 13 rebounds for the Lancers (6-13, 2-4 Big South), who won their second in row. Longwood scored the first seven of the second half to lead 44-27, building on an 11-point halftime lead. Campbell (8-9, 2-5) closed back to within 11 at 50-39, but the Lancers answered with an 8-0 run and led by no less than 17 the rest of the way. Chris Clemons had 22 points to lead the Camels. Troy Harper and D.J. Mason added 13 points each. Darrion Allen added 11 points for Longwood, which shot 55.2 percent from the field while Campbell made just 32.8 percent.
